# scaffold-linter: shell
# Shellcheck enforces correctness for shell scripts — its default checks flag
# real bugs (quoting, unset vars, unsafe rm, etc.). We deliberately do NOT set
# `enable=all`: the optional checks it adds (SC2250 ${var} braces, SC2292 [[ ]]
# over [ ]) are stylistic, not correctness, and shipping a config the vendored
# scripts themselves can't satisfy is worse than enforcing nothing.
# Quantitative metrics (file length, magic numbers) are covered by the
# scaffold mechanical check (check-quality-mechanical.sh) for .sh/.bash files.
#
# The lint workflow gates on warning-level and above (genuine bugs: unsafe rm,
# unset expansion, bad redirects) via the action's `severity: warning` input —
# `severity` is not a valid .shellcheckrc directive. Info-level findings
# (e.g. SC2015 `A && B || C` in test assertions) stay advisory, not failures.
